<item>
            <title>[PIG-340] Specifying &apos;using PigStorage(&apos;\t&apos;)&apos; in a script causes pig to fail</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-340</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The script &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;A = load &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;/user/pig/tests/data/perf/studenttab200m&apos;&lt;/span&gt; using PigStorage(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;\t&apos;&lt;/span&gt;) as (name, age, gpa);
B = filter A by gpa &amp;lt; 3.6;
store B into &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;filter10pct2&apos;&lt;/span&gt; using PigStorage();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;fails with the error message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        at org.apache.pig.backend.hadoop.executionengine.mapReduceLayer.PigMapOnly$Map.map(PigMapOnly.java:64)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.hadoop.mapred.MapRunner.run(MapRunner.java:47)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.hadoop.mapred.MapTask.run(MapTask.java:219)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.hadoop.mapred.TaskTracker$Child.main(TaskTracker.java:2124)&lt;br/&gt;
 java.io.IOException: Request for field number 2 exceeds tuple size of 1&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.pig.backend.hadoop.executionengine.mapReduceLayer.PigMapBase.map(PigMapBase.java:139)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.pig.backend.hadoop.executionengine.mapReduceLayer.PigMapOnly$Map.map(PigMapOnly.java:64)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.hadoop.mapred.MapRunner.run(MapRunner.java:47)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.hadoop.mapred.MapTask.run(MapTask.java:219)&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.hadoop.mapred.TaskTracker$Child.main(TaskTracker.java:2124)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;while&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;A = load &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;/user/pig/tests/data/perf/studenttab200m&apos;&lt;/span&gt; as (name, age, gpa);
B = filter A by gpa &amp;lt; 3.6;
store B into &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;filter10pct2&apos;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;runs just fine over the same data.  It appears that the specification of the load function or the delimiter is causing issues.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
